




how to create whatsup button


http://codersspot.in/how-add-whatsapp-chat-to-the-website/




1. include the font-awesome CSS to your website.   # no need for this link in google blogger
 
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.5.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">


# we can add this at the desired place
2. add the below HTML code in your footer and change the anchor tag value with your country code and Whatsapp number.


<a href="https://wa.me/country_code_and_your_phone_number" class="whatsapp_float" target="_blank"> <i class="fa fa-whatsapp whatsapp-icon"></i></a>


# we have to add this at the top section of the blogger as there the css code is
3. Add the below CSS code


/* for desktop */
.whatsapp_float {
	position:fixed;
	width:60px;
	height:60px;
	bottom:40px;
	right:40px;
	background-color:#25d366;
	color:#FFF;
	border-radius:50px;
	text-align:center;
        font-size:30px;
	box-shadow: 2px 2px 3px #999;
        z-index:100;
}

.whatsapp-icon {
	margin-top:16px;
}
/* for mobile */
@media screen and (max-width: 767px){
     .whatsapp-icon {
	 margin-top:10px;
     }
    .whatsapp_float {
        width: 40px;
        height: 40px;
        bottom: 20px;
        right: 10px;
        font-size: 22px;
    }
}
